  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Private Seed Sector Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Private Seed Sector Development (PSSD) project aims to double production and income of 108.000 farmer households in Burundi by ensuring sustainable access to certified seeds and agricultural advisory services. The project is a private sector development (PSD) project that will incentivize and support Burundian and international seed companies to pilot innovations related to seed production and sales.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will focus on the development of sales strategies that are tailored to farmer household requirements. This includes: 1. The sale of seeds in micro-packs 2. Development of last-mile distribution capabilities a. Rural points of sales (POS) b. Mobile sales agents 3. Micro-demonstration plots 4. Consumer education-focused communication strategies tailored to farmers 5. Development of specialized promotional materials tailored to farmers The project will moreover support seed companies to increase production efficiencies though the provision of technical and targeted financial support for: 1. Critical infrastructure upgrades 2. Intensification of production PSSD will furthermore support initiatives to improve the business-enabling environment in relation to seed production and sales in Burundi. The project will among others target: 1. Liberalization of seed prices 2. Improvement of seed inspection and certification services 3. Policy coherency in relation to variety release and registration</narrative>
  </description>
